# --- NS-3 raw run outputs ---
# Big/reproducible artifacts: ignored EVERYWHERE (incl. my-work/).
*.pcap
network-anim*.xml
iproute-anim*.xml
# FlowMonitor XML: ignore only stray copies at the repo ROOT & scratch runs;
# curated ones under my-work/ (leading slash = root-anchored) stay TRACKED.
/flowmonitor-stats*.xml
/*.flowmon.xml

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
venv/

# --- Local-only working context (not part of the fork) ---
CLAUDE.md
docs/

# --- OS / editor cruft ---
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# Report drafts (local). Hand-edited working documents, superseded by a single
# consolidated report. Listed by name rather than as IoMT-*.docx so that the final
# report is not silently ignored along with them.
IoMT-Yontem-ve-Kararlar-Raporu.docx
IoMT-Degerlendirme-ve-EDA-Raporu.docx
IoMT-Gurultu-ve-Tasarim-Kararlari-Raporu.docx
IoMT-Progress-Report-2026-07-21.docx
IoMT-Simulasyon-Tabani-ve-Yeni-Veri-Seti-Raporu.docx

# Per-stage report generators: each writes a .docx from scratch, while those reports
# themselves are hand-edited and kept out of the repo. Keeping them tracked invites
# regenerating over the edits. Scoped to the day folders on purpose -- the
# consolidated report's generator in my-work/report/ IS tracked, because there the
# source of truth is the tracked Markdown and the .docx is a build product.
my-work/day*/make_report.py

# The consolidated report's build product. Regenerated from the tracked Markdown by
# my-work/report/make_report.py, and hand-finished afterwards (cover, contents, page
# numbers) -- so the file on disk is not always what the generator would produce.
my-work/report/*.docx

# LibreOffice lock files, created while a csv is open in the GUI
.~lock.*#
my-work/report/*.docx.built
